00:48:20.210 --> 00:48:24.830
healthcare policies. And even truly perhaps
the last word has not said. And there's going

00:48:24.830 --> 00:48:30.070
to be an election in the next few months and
maybe people will have a chance to speak,

00:48:30.070 --> 00:48:35.530
speak up. And, I'm, I'm sure there'll be a
sequel to that. That is the stuff of politics.

00:48:35.530 --> 00:48:40.030
In India, I don't recall, I'm not sure if
I can recall a single instance when a Prime

00:48:40.030 --> 00:48:45.030
Minister ever addressed the country on a single
issue of say, how to educate our people? How

00:48:45.030 --> 00:48:48.650
to improve the quality of healthcare? Or anything
else for that matter.

00:48:48.650 --> 00:48:55.220
So we have to redefine politics and unless
the middle classes are deeply engaged, and

00:48:55.220 --> 00:49:02.230
unless they learn the art of pursuit of personal
goals along with pursuit of public good simultaneously,

00:49:02.230 --> 00:49:07.330
we have problem. Somewhere we have to break
this logjam. Politicians, there's no point

00:49:07.330 --> 00:49:11.890
blaming them, I know we all love to hate politicians.
Everybody, even in the United States, everybody

00:49:11.890 --> 00:49:17.160
loves to hate a Congressman or politician.
