00:53:46.710 --> 00:53:51.570
not strong in India, they're probably stronger
in India than China. So I would like to have

00:53:51.570 --> 00:53:53.290
your thoughts about why does --

00:53:53.290 --> 00:53:54.290
&gt;&gt;JP:
OK

00:53:54.290 --> 00:53:56.640
&gt;&gt;audience4:
work in China? That's question number one.

00:53:56.640 --> 00:54:04.570
Question number two is about the Maoist Insurgents
in India. Even people like [inaudible] are

00:54:04.570 --> 00:54:12.750
coming out saying that because of this abject
failure of governments and there even the

00:54:12.750 --> 00:54:17.060
Maoists are out there; violence might be the
only answer that the people there might have

00:54:17.060 --> 00:54:18.060
against the Indians--

00:54:18.060 --> 00:54:20.840
&gt;&gt;JP:
Good questions, but--

00:54:20.840 --> 00:54:23.610
&gt;&gt;audience4:
I don't, I don't agree with him, I just want

00:54:23.610 --> 00:54:24.610
your thoughts--

00:54:24.610 --> 00:54:27.420
&gt;&gt;JP:
I understand. First about Fareed Zakaria and

00:54:27.420 --> 00:54:32.120
China's rule of law and absence of it. Now,
when I made a comparison between India and

00:54:32.120 --> 00:54:41.780
China, I did just to caution the Indian scholars
and others who consistently argue that we

00:54:41.780 --> 00:54:47.010
are so democratic and wonderful that we have
nothing to change. It is not to argue that

00:54:47.010 --> 00:54:51.100
China is better than India in that respect.
That would be a foolish argument.

00:54:51.100 --> 00:54:56.070
All I'm arguing is that there are factions
in Chinese governance which are perhaps more

00:54:56.070 --> 00:55:03.530
democratic than in a liberal, free Indian
society. Overcentralization has been our bane.

00:55:03.530 --> 00:55:08.960
Decentralization has been their strength.
Decentralization by definition is democratization.

00:55:08.960 --> 00:55:12.480
A total democratization. In India, we have
not yet done it.

00:55:12.480 --> 00:55:17.840
Obviously, rule of law is far more deficient
in China than in India. In India, the instruments

00:55:17.840 --> 00:55:22.150
of rule of law are really very strong; they're
there. The delivery is weak for a variety

00:55:22.150 --> 00:55:26.130
of reasons we have to now set that right.
But in other ways, the acceptance of rule

00:55:26.130 --> 00:55:32.220
of law as a notion, as a norm, are the instruments
of rule of law a constitutional and legal

00:55:32.220 --> 00:55:37.430
instruments of rule of law, we are ages ahead
of China. There's no question, but still we

00:55:37.430 --> 00:55:39.430
have to set something straight.

00:55:39.430 --> 00:55:45.370
Obviously, what we have to demonstrate to
the world is that freedom and economic growth

00:55:45.370 --> 00:55:49.040
are compatible. Democracy is not related to
growth because some people are now coming

00:55:49.040 --> 00:55:55.980
to the dangerous conclusion that growth in
an emerging economy means autocracy. So why

00:55:55.980 --> 00:55:59.890
I argue, so why I'm arguing that China is
invested democratic is, is democratic impulses

00:55:59.890 --> 00:56:03.950
of China that actually led to growth, not
autocratic impulses. You must see both of

00:56:03.950 --> 00:56:04.950
them together.

00:56:04.950 --> 00:56:14.840
Otherwise, I agree. But I'm not very, a great
fan of the notion of Fareeh Zakaria, that

00:56:14.840 --> 00:56:20.901
you must increasingly view power to the unelected.
I recognize the importance of the unelected

00:56:20.901 --> 00:56:27.190
institutions like the Supreme Court, like
the Election Commission, etc. But the think

00:56:27.190 --> 00:56:32.350
that you can somehow solve the problems of
politics by nonpolitical institutions is a

00:56:32.350 --> 00:56:36.030
typical bureaucratic or middle class approach.

00:56:36.030 --> 00:56:41.350
There is no substitute to politics. Clean,
decent politics, mobilizing public opinion,

00:56:41.350 --> 00:56:45.630
and more and more and better and better people
playing a creative role; being deeply engaged

00:56:45.630 --> 00:56:50.740
as citizens and as, as people who would influence
the outcomes of the local level and the state

00:56:50.740 --> 00:56:56.580
and national level. There's no substitute
to that. And the danger is, and somehow believing

00:56:56.580 --> 00:56:59.620
that because we have a Supreme Court, we have
an Election Commission, or some other strong

00:56:59.620 --> 00:57:04.000
body, everything will be alright. My friend,
Seshan, a very good personal friend, even

00:57:04.000 --> 00:57:09.220
today, and since has very few friends remaining
actually, he's a good man but not very strong

00:57:09.220 --> 00:57:14.890
and sometimes a civic man. He was a great
Election Commissioner. What did he prove?

00:57:14.890 --> 00:57:19.510
He proved that the constitutional lawist in
India could be autonomous if they really,

00:57:19.510 --> 00:57:25.800
sought, sought to be so. If they chose to
be so. He proved that they could actually

00:57:25.800 --> 00:57:30.790
be independent. But, could he change the nature
of elections in India? Far from it. Seshan

00:57:30.790 --> 00:57:32.820
himself knows that. It's not his failure.

00:57:32.820 --> 00:57:38.580
After all, the constitution itself is a creation
of the constitution and a law of the land.

00:57:38.580 --> 00:57:43.691
The Parliament gives the mandate for the Election
Commission to function. It can only function

00:57:43.691 --> 00:57:48.830
within that. It has no mandate to go beyond
that. Therefore, to think that somehow by

00:57:48.830 --> 00:57:52.880
investing so much authority and prestige and
hope in them, we can solve the problems of

00:57:52.880 --> 00:57:58.090
India, we'd comitting a great mistake. They
are necessary, but they're not sufficient.

00:57:58.090 --> 00:58:04.670
Ultimately, politics have to be set by politics.
About Maoists, I'm glad you asked this question.

00:58:04.670 --> 00:58:09.450
Undoubtedly, the failure of governance in
India are in capacity to fulfill the aspirations

00:58:09.450 --> 00:58:14.000
of the bulk of the people. And the fact that
the accident of birth is determined in the

00:58:14.000 --> 00:58:20.250
future by the bulk of the children. These
are the fuel; these are the fodder for generating

00:58:20.250 --> 00:58:26.100
any number of violent moments. Some of them
turned to be Maoist; that's not the only one.

00:58:26.100 --> 00:58:32.730
We have recognized that, but having recognized
that if we do not also recognize that in a

00:58:32.730 --> 00:58:38.280
democratic society where the constitutional
liberty are available and vote is available,

00:58:38.280 --> 00:58:44.470
the only forum of dissent, form of dissent
is within the bounds of the constitution.

00:58:44.470 --> 00:58:50.920
Namely, you holler, you shout, you protest,
you demonstrate without obstructing others,

00:58:50.920 --> 00:58:55.180
without disrupting other peoples freedoms,
in front of the White House. When I went the

00:58:55.180 --> 00:59:00.801
other day, I saw; found two groups of people
with the banners about all kinds of things.

00:59:00.801 --> 00:59:05.640
That is legitimate democratic protest, its
basis is provided and they continue to try

00:59:05.640 --> 00:59:10.140
and attract public attention and eventually,
as even politicians recognize that they cannot

00:59:10.140 --> 00:59:12.290
ignore that issue, they will address that.

00:59:12.290 --> 00:59:17.060
That is democracy. All else should feel sufficiently
mad about it, like some of the nice Hollywood

00:59:17.060 --> 00:59:21.760
films. Somebody gets into Congress and moves
the Congress and the nation and something

00:59:21.760 --> 00:59:26.420
about it. That's all politics is about. But
if I say that because I'm not happy with the

00:59:26.420 --> 00:59:30.250
way things are, I will take to the gun, I
will extinguish the liberties available under

00:59:30.250 --> 00:59:35.250
the Constitution, I'll take law into my hands,
and I will, in fact, repeal this constitution

00:59:35.250 --> 00:59:39.900
instead of abolish the constitution itself.
That's not acceptable. Therefore, the state

00:59:39.900 --> 00:59:46.530
and the people have every right and duty to
do everything within the bounds of the constitution

00:59:46.530 --> 00:59:52.970
to control it. Let there be no mistake, whatsoever.
Abraham Lincoln had this question repeatedly

00:59:52.970 --> 00:59:58.590
posed to him during the Civil War. He said
time and again if the first article of the

00:59:58.590 --> 01:00:01.760
American Constitution collapses, all else
fails.

01:00:01.760 --> 01:00:04.870
Therefore, in order to preserve the first
article, namely the union, there should be

01:00:04.870 --> 01:00:12.290
union of states. I will do whatever it takes.
Just like there is a hierarchy of principles

01:00:12.290 --> 01:00:16.260
or hierarchy of needs, there is also a hierarchy
of principles. The ultimate principle for

01:00:16.260 --> 01:00:20.830
the state is to preserve the Constitutional
order. Everything else is to become subordinate

01:00:20.830 --> 01:00:26.980
to that. Having said that, merely by doing
whatever it takes to control them is it enough?

01:00:26.980 --> 01:00:31.280
No. We also have to create a just order, give
confidence to the bulk of the people that,

01:00:31.280 --> 01:00:36.820
"Look, we understand your agony. We hear your
voice, we created a framework which more just

01:00:36.820 --> 01:00:41.110
and more humane and it's not even perfect,
it's always work in progress, but everybody

01:00:41.110 --> 01:00:47.720
has a chance." I don't agree with, the author
at all in this respect. I know, you don't

01:00:47.720 --> 01:00:52.890
either. It's very dangerous not to use arguments
without understanding the context. She's able

01:00:52.890 --> 01:00:55.460
to speak out because she's at liberty.

01:00:55.460 --> 01:01:00.070
What happened in Cambodia, please remember.
When Pol Pot was in power, one third of all

01:01:00.070 --> 01:01:06.010
Cambodian people were decimated. The youngest
child was first killed so that the rest of

01:01:06.010 --> 01:01:11.590
the family understood the pain. The fellow
with glasses, somebody like you or me, just

01:01:11.590 --> 01:01:16.181
because you wore glasses, the fact that you
wore glasses means that you are, you are not

01:01:16.181 --> 01:01:20.470
a hard working man. You're not a liberal.
They feel you are dangerous to society. They

01:01:20.470 --> 01:01:25.410
killed them. The people with soft hands; they
were killed. One after the whole family was

01:01:25.410 --> 01:01:31.670
killed. One third of the whole country was
butchered by its own government. It never

01:01:31.670 --> 01:01:39.730
happened in history, not even Hitler did that.
If that is how a notion of a future, I don't

01:01:39.730 --> 01:01:46.520
think any Indian wants it. Because of temporary
anger about the injustices on occasion we

01:01:46.520 --> 01:01:53.670
may say, "Oh, next race is better." But no.
It's a dangerous argument. As long as freedom

01:01:53.670 --> 01:01:58.410
is there, as long as vote is there, there's
only one route, there's, there's only one

01:01:58.410 --> 01:01:59.410
road.

01:01:59.410 --> 01:02:04.760
That man may not be recorded but they have
some questions I'll be happy to take. It's

01:02:04.760 --> 01:02:05.760
up to you.

01:02:05.760 --> 01:02:11.100
Ok, ok, ok. I'll just take that question.

01:02:11.100 --> 01:02:13.820
&gt;&gt;male audience5:
[Indian accent]

01:02:13.820 --> 01:02:19.390
You recently become the MLA in, in some region.
So, I'd like to know some of the positive

01:02:19.390 --> 01:02:24.840
experiences you had in like, typical Indian
movies and Indian literature, the recent one.

01:02:24.840 --> 01:02:29.950
They depict Indian politics as something really
nasty, something really dirty. Actually, you've

01:02:29.950 --> 01:02:35.810
met some people at some, at least civilians
who were nice to you, who actually abided

01:02:35.810 --> 01:02:41.040
by the line, give you a kind of positive spirit
like, "Yes, there are people who want a change."

01:02:41.040 --> 01:02:43.130
I'd like to know more about that.

01:02:43.130 --> 01:02:49.660
&gt;&gt;JP:
Ok. First of all, we must have a, a broader

01:02:49.660 --> 01:02:56.280
argument. Are politicians necessarily scoundrels?
Does it mean that the scum of humanity in

01:02:56.280 --> 01:03:00.300
this politics and all the nice people and
nice people are outside politics? Are there

01:03:00.300 --> 01:03:06.070
two groups of society? Or, are politicians
doing, in a set of circumstances, whatever

01:03:06.070 --> 01:03:12.550
they think they should do in order to try?
We must have some clarity. I would plead with

01:03:12.550 --> 01:03:18.620
you to recognize that politicians are just
another set of human beings.

01:03:18.620 --> 01:03:23.780
They are not a very specialized set of corrupt,
rotten, criminal human beings, they are human

01:03:23.780 --> 01:03:30.840
beings. Period. If you create an institutional
framework where by doing what is right you

01:03:30.840 --> 01:03:36.300
can also politically prosper, they would happily
do that. The Prime Ministers, the Chief Ministers,

01:03:36.300 --> 01:03:41.950
the MPs and MLAs of India, they are not taking
a vow to destroy India. They are taking a

01:03:41.950 --> 01:03:45.950
vow to do whatever it takes to get, to get
into power. And to do whatever it takes to

01:03:45.950 --> 01:03:51.110
stay in power. It's for us to create a system
where you can do something honorable and decent

01:03:51.110 --> 01:03:55.710
and public-spirited and yet, be politically
relevant.

01:03:55.710 --> 01:03:59.420
If you consistently prove that by doing the
nice thing and the right thing, you're politically

01:03:59.420 --> 01:04:04.320
irrelevant. We are actually driving them to
do something wrong. My experience proved this

01:04:04.320 --> 01:04:10.050
to be absolutely true. Most of the fellow
legislators of my, in my provincial assembly,

01:04:10.050 --> 01:04:17.920
80% of them at least, almost everybody, with
exception of myself, they have paid money

01:04:17.920 --> 01:04:22.760
to get the vote. It's, it's universally known.
But despite that, they recognize that they

01:04:22.760 --> 01:04:26.980
have become victims of a vicious cycle. Given
a choice, given a chance, they'll actually

01:04:26.980 --> 01:04:30.872
do something nice and decent. They despair
all the time, but they feel that they are

01:04:30.872 --> 01:04:35.130
in the vicious cycle they can't get out of
the trap easily. So, they're not villains.

01:04:35.130 --> 01:04:41.770
And my faith is vindicated. But, will they
always behave in a manner that, that really

01:04:41.770 --> 01:04:45.870
oppose their views? No. Because they're creatures
of their own parties, they're slaves of their

01:04:45.870 --> 01:04:50.720
party, and they're slaves of the power game.
And they simply feel that there's no escape

01:04:50.720 --> 01:04:51.720
from that.

01:04:51.720 --> 01:04:58.040
So, unless there is external pressure and
pull, and unless we, we mobilize the society

01:04:58.040 --> 01:05:04.480
and prove that clean politics and honesty
are compatible with survival in our public

01:05:04.480 --> 01:05:10.460
office; I don't think we can change that.
I'll conclude the comment with one last word.

01:05:10.460 --> 01:05:19.470
We have in India today a phenomenal opportunity.
We have the technology, thanks to all of you,

01:05:19.470 --> 01:05:23.931
the world is virtually flat, and we can access
almost everything that's happening almost

01:05:23.931 --> 01:05:28.020
anywhere in the world; get knowledge of a
kind which would be unbelievable earlier.

01:05:28.020 --> 01:05:33.530
We have the resources, may not be enough to
have an American standard of living, which

01:05:33.530 --> 01:05:39.150
probably is crazy anyway. It's too high. It's
not possible for the whole globe, but we have

01:05:39.150 --> 01:05:44.850
enough resources to be able to fulfill all
the basic needs of Indian people and to give

01:05:44.850 --> 01:05:48.100
opportunity for us to fulfill our potential
as a country.

01:05:48.100 --> 01:05:53.630
What we lack are institutions. What we lack
is the right kind of politics. And with all

01:05:53.630 --> 01:05:57.700
these institutions, technology plant, can
be transplanted easily. Institutions like

01:05:57.700 --> 01:06:03.200
take a lot of nurturing. Institutions take
a lot of public pressure. Institutions take

01:06:03.200 --> 01:06:08.890
the middle classes and the educated people
to be engaged; deeply and on a sustained basis.

01:06:08.890 --> 01:06:14.550
What I'm arguing is, let us be engaged because
our future is on the line. And in a fundamental

01:06:14.550 --> 01:06:18.410
sense, the mankind's truthfulness is on the
line. There's no reason for cynicism and despair

01:06:18.410 --> 01:06:23.460
at all. On occasion it appears to be exceedingly
difficult, but there are forces of change.

01:06:23.460 --> 01:06:28.251
The young people are increasingly more confident,
they believe that they can change their country;

01:06:28.251 --> 01:06:33.780
they're idealistic whether they live in India
or abroad. Economic growth itself is actually

01:06:33.780 --> 01:06:38.520
spurring forces of change in the country.
It's going to make many people ask uncomfortable

01:06:38.520 --> 01:06:43.600
questions and the communications evolution
that all of you have had is reaching in you

01:06:43.600 --> 01:06:50.930
also, many Indians, including the ordinary,
poor, shop owners, and, and hard workers.

01:06:50.930 --> 01:06:54.790
And all these will ultimately bring about
a fundamental change, but the question is

01:06:54.790 --> 01:06:58.980
what direction of change it'll take? That
depends on what we do now. That's why I gave

01:06:58.980 --> 01:07:04.171
you the most great example. If we do the right
thing together, today, if we give confidence,

01:07:04.171 --> 01:07:07.940
then that change will be the right one. Otherwise,
change will anyway happen, but not the, not

01:07:07.940 --> 01:07:12.810
necessarily the right one. I ask a few in
our own enlightened self-interest, interest

01:07:12.810 --> 01:07:18.100
of India, and in a larger sense an interest
with the broader humanity. We worked ourselves

01:07:18.100 --> 01:07:21.971
to make a difference to the way the Indian
political trajectory takes shape. Thank you

01:07:21.971 --> 01:07:23.690
very much.

01:07:23.690 --> 01:07:24.550
[applause]

